{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe additive model and its back-compat/lifecycle invariants must be locked by tests.\n## What\nCover all invariants end to end (integration tests require all prior children merged).\n## Scope\n`tests/interfaces/lifecycle/` (coexistence, reopen validity), reducer/compaction unit tests,\n`tests/unit/test_signing.py`.\n## Depends on\nRequires 114f, 2c2d, cc1b, 929e merged (integration over the full surface).\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Test: plan-review + close retains both kinds; re-sign a kind replaces in place.\n- [ ] Test: compaction/SNAPSHOT round-trip preserves all kinds.\n- [ ] Test: legacy single-signature ticket reads/verifies via fold-in; a NEW snapshot is readable by old-code (mirror present).\n- [ ] Test: reopen makes completion (and plan-review) read not-valid; records unchanged; re-close re-signs.\n- [ ] Test: a material-field edit after signing invalidates completion validity; a tag/assignee edit does NOT.\n- [ ] Test: concurrent different-kind signs both survive (per-key LWW convergence).\n- [ ] Test: no HMAC hex appears in `show`/MCP public output for any attestation kind."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782795417638852001,"uuid":"4a1c5108-594f-42dc-9ed2-19a8ba71daf5"}